Ε. 3351), 11. 14-18. Si patema. . . .termiao 01 aapra. Ut capra is omitted in a number of the manuscripts which contaIn the passage3 MD adda, de termino Paachoe uana regni regia Hearici octavo. Regular in OD, OF, OG, MD. Inserted aster dictura eat, l. 9, in MC; aster iudicium, l. 12, 10 OM, ΟΜ. MarginaIInOA, LA, Omitted in OB, ΟΟ, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΙ, ΟΕ, Y. This is avery blind reference, quite unlike Bracton's usual citation; but inasmuch as the passage is so generally vouched for by the manuscripts in (ΙΙ) and (ΙΙΙ), we can hardly do otherwise than ascribe it to him. It may well be that in the original note a space was 1011 aster termino to be filled in later with the correct reference. In at least one of the manuscripts such a space is to be found. The reference 10 the year and term in MD was in all probability not added by Bracton (it would be given in other manuscripts were that the case), but it is important as showing how later users of the treatise could make a citation in Bracton's typical form.
